Sentencas: The electrochemical behavior of pure lanthanum chromite and strontium dopedlanthanum chromite was studied by impedance spectroscopy under H(2)/H(2)O, CO/CO(2) and CH(4)/H(2)O. Results show that the electrochemical oxidation of H(2) is faster than that of CO or CH(4).
Titulo: Lanthanum Chromite as an Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Strontium doping enhances the anodic activity of the material.
Titulo: Lanthanum Chromite as an Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The impedance diagrams are composed of two semi-circles.
Titulo: Lanthanum Chromite as an Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The high frequency one does not appear to be related to a chemical or electrochemical reaction.
Titulo: Lanthanum Chromite as an Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The low frequency one is linked to the nature and concentration of the electroactive species.
Titulo: Lanthanum Chromite as an Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
